<subSubSection id="482733CF3BDA98199A17FBA6C143F12B" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D11175DCBE10C79D08A1508553078B17" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6F2E294A96A7F8F8F37C9CB85D956765" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New record: East Rhodopes, Meden buk vill., 22.04.2021, 12 w., leg. ALG. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="6DFB98A89C064A8BCE4344C4C45C8EEA" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4DE4443F71472636E8F508F4CEB59DDB" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B80336680B640C7CA72FFB2C512A814E" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="28D6E49D724232F738531CC37A1F663D" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
At least three morphospecies close to 
<taxonomicName id="F2123BE04BB4746703D672BBC4908808" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1861" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tetramorium punicum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punicum">
<emphasis id="703897F06775BD14589258337E47CF35" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Tetramorium punicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Smith, 1861), described from Israel, have been distinguished in the southern Balkans and the Greek islands. Accurate identification of this species complex requires the study of sexual castes. As our material consists only of workers, the species-level determination is not possible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
